{"type":"message","id":"aace1a72","parentId":"1556921f","timestamp":"2026-04-28T14:13:01.343Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is saying that I'm telling him about emails that have already been scanned. Looking at the replied message, I sent him an email about \"RC Leasing — Re: Looking for new apartment\" and told him Logan needs to finish his part.\n\nIt seems like Bobby is saying he already knew about this email or already saw it, and I keep telling him about it again. This sounds like a duplicate/rescan issue with my email checking.\n\nI should acknowledge this and figure out what's happening. Let me check my recent email scan history or cron jobs to understand the issue.\n\nThe issue is likely that my hourly email check cron is re-reporting old emails. I should look at:\n1. How I'm tracking what's \"new\" vs already reported\n\n\n2. My hourly email check script or cron setup\n\nLet me check my email scanning setup to understand why I'm re-reporting emails.","thinkingSignature":"43ea1193a2f5118efe52b3f2acb57aa7fd2854f27b39902042edc35147875617"},{"type":"text","text":"That's frustrating — I apologize for the repeat. Let me check how I'm tracking what's already been reported vs what's actually new.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_37tgs6yby6zz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/Desktop/SecondBrain/Workspace/ | grep -i email"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_37tgs6yby6zz_2","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"list","includeDisabled":true}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":172,"output":271,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":27003,"totalTokens":27446,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777385566083,"responseId":"063ff35ecd66feccb43377eb92913f6f"}}
