{"type":"message","id":"36d5448f","parentId":"aa5dfa7e","timestamp":"2026-04-28T14:13:26.602Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the problem better. Looking at the cron job for iCloud email check:\n\nThe iCloud check uses `himalaya envelope list --account icloud` without any time filter. Unlike Gmail which has `newer_than:1h`, himalaya doesn't have that capability built into the envelope list command.\n\nThe issue is that I'm not tracking which iCloud emails I've already notified Bobby about. Each time the cron runs, I'm checking all iCloud emails and potentially re-notifying about emails I've already sent.\n\nFor Gmail, the cron uses `newer_than:1h` which is better but still might pick up some overlap if there's a scan every hour.\n\n\nI need to set up a checkpoint file to record the most recent iCloud email I already notified about, then only alert on anything newer than that on the next run.","thinkingSignature":"61d66044fd3d0f8cc373b997569c62f05fa551ecfe5f56bee1b224724ee86fa8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5hmvf19s12z7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp && echo \"---\" && cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_summary.txt"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":10218,"output":227,"cacheRead":26709,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37154,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777385598763,"responseId":"063ff37ede84037734ad2b8ade117c9a"}}
