{"type":"message","id":"cf7cbe4c","parentId":"4bb3121b","timestamp":"2026-04-28T14:18:17.350Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is complaining again that I'm reporting emails from iCloud that have already been scanned. The issue is clear from my previous investigation:\n\n1. The \"Emmy Email Check (Gmail + iCloud)\" cron job runs hourly\n2. For iCloud, it runs `himalaya envelope list --account icloud` with NO date filter - it lists ALL envelopes\n3. There's no checkpoint/state file tracking what's already been reported for iCloud\n4. Gmail avoids this by using `newer_than:1h` in the search query, but iCloud doesn't have that luxury with himalaya\n\nThe solution is to track the last time we checked iCloud and only report emails newer than that. I need to update the cron job's payload to track a timestamp for iCloud specifically.\n\nLet me get the current cron job ID for the email check and update it with a proper fix that:\n1. Saves the current time BEFORE checking\n2. Only shows emails newer than the last check time for iCloud","thinkingSignature":"e21981337aa0617c829cd093b7b553560d42d2ff5f163bfbf7f324f23bc62f70"},{"type":"text","text":"\nGot it — the iCloud check has no \"already seen\" tracking. Let me fix it properly now.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ma15ndl1t35n_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_check.timestamp 2>/dev/null || echo \"NO_FILE\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":172,"output":277,"cacheRead":26709,"cacheWrite":8836,"totalTokens":35994,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777385881217,"responseId":"063ff499f55616e7e1d836783e1e8af2"}}
