{"type":"message","id":"28ede643","parentId":"a6128b5d","timestamp":"2026-04-28T14:19:20.061Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The most recent email has ID 10. So I can track the last reported ID in a file, and only show emails with ID > last reported ID.\n\nLet me create the updated cron job message that:1. Reads the last reported ID from `~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_id.txt`2. Lists iCloud emails sorted by date desc\n3. Only processes emails with ID > last reported ID\n4. After sending, updates the last reported ID to the highest ID processed\n\nHere's the updated message for the cron job:","thinkingSignature":"6782f12c61c430917450551adf9d988d20ddebcde3108c839ddcb527ca285a3b"},{"type":"text","text":"Good — emails have IDs (10, 9, 8...) sorted newest first. I'll track the last-seen ID in a file and only report strictly newer emails.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ed3o3tkshynk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"10\" > ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_id.txt && echo \"Set initial iCloud checkpoint to ID 10 (most recent email)\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":15240,"output":208,"cacheRead":26709,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42157,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777385948885,"responseId":"063ff4ddfb09a9bce3efdea17feca5fd"}}
